    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral RCC",
        "description": "SVD-decoded RCC peripheral dump on attached target"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "This maps to `stm32 debug read-peripheral RCC` (DBG-007) \u2014 spawns a fresh gdbserver + arm-gdb, halts the target, SVD-decodes the full RCC peripheral, tears down, and emits JSON. ELF is autodiscovered from `stm32-project.jsonc`.\nThe gdbserver exited before becoming ready. The ST-LINK firmware on the probe is out of date and needs to be upgraded before the session can start.\n\n**Error:** `ST-LINK firmware upgrade required`\n**Root cause:** The onboard ST-LINK reports it requires a firmware upgrade (gdbserver exit code 6). This is a known condition on this bench board \u2014 the onboard ST-Link V2J28M17 emits a firmware-upgrade demand; it also appears in your memory note as the `DEV_USB_COMM_ERR` bench F401RE.\n\n---\n\n**Next step \u2014 upgrade the ST-LINK firmware:**\n\n1. Open **STM32CubeProgrammer** GUI \u2192 top-right **\"Firmware upgrade\"** button (or `STM32_Programmer_CLI --upgrade`), or\n2. Use **ST-LINK Upgrade** utility (`ST-LinkUpgrade.exe` / `ST-LinkUpgrade` on Linux).\n\nOnce upgraded, re-run the same command and the RCC peripheral dump will proceed:\n\n```\nstm32 debug read-peripheral RCC\n```\n\nWould you like me to invoke the ST-LINK firmware upgrade via `STM32_Programmer_CLI` now?"
}